# Shopify Theme Development Guidelines

## **Project Initialization**
- **Use Shopify Skeleton Theme as Foundation**: Always start with [skeleton-theme](https://github.com/Shopify/skeleton-theme.git) for new projects
- **Development Environment Setup**:
  ```bash
  # Initialize theme
  shopify theme init my-theme-name
  cd my-theme-name
  
  # Start development server
  shopify theme dev --store {store-name}
  
  # Preview at http://127.0.0.1:9292
  ```
- **Required Tools**: Shopify CLI, VS Code with Shopify Liquid extension
- **MCP Server Integration**: Use shopify-mcp-server for store connection and API operations

## **Theme Architecture Standards**
- **Follow Skeleton Theme Structure**:
  ```
  ├── assets/          # Static assets (CSS, JS, images, fonts)
  ├── blocks/          # Reusable, nestable UI components  
  ├── config/          # Global theme settings
  ├── layout/          # Top-level page wrappers
  ├── locales/         # Translation files
  ├── sections/        # Modular full-width components
  ├── snippets/        # Reusable Liquid/HTML fragments
  └── templates/       # Page structure definitions (JSON templates)
  ```

## **Component Development**
- **Sections with Schema**:
  ```liquid
  {% comment %} ✅ DO: Include comprehensive schema {% endcomment %}
  <section class="hero {{ section.settings.layout }}" style="--gap: {{ section.settings.gap }}px">
    <!-- Section content -->
  </section>

  {% schema %}
  {
    "name": "Hero Section",
    "settings": [
      {
        "type": "select",
        "id": "layout",
        "label": "Layout",
        "options": [
          { "value": "hero--full-width", "label": "Full Width" },
          { "value": "hero--narrow", "label": "Narrow" }
        ],
        "default": "hero--full-width"
      },
      {
        "type": "range",
        "id": "gap",
        "label": "Gap",
        "min": 0,
        "max": 100,
        "step": 5,
        "unit": "px",
        "default": 20
      }
    ],
    "blocks": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "name": "Heading",
        "settings": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "id": "title",
            "label": "Title"
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "presets": [
      {
        "name": "Hero Section",
        "blocks": [
          {
            "type": "heading"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
  {% endschema %}
  ```

- **Blocks Structure**:
  ```liquid
  {% comment %} ✅ DO: Create flexible, reusable blocks {% endcomment %}
  <div class="block-{{ block.type }} {{ block.settings.alignment }}">
    {% case block.type %}
      {% when 'heading' %}
        <h{{ block.settings.heading_level }} class="heading">
          {{ block.settings.title }}
        </h{{ block.settings.heading_level }}>
      {% when 'text' %}
        <div class="text-content">
          {{ block.settings.content }}
        </div>
    {% endcase %}
  </div>
  ```

## **CSS & JavaScript Best Practices**
- **Use Embedded Styles**: Prefer `{% stylesheet %}` and `{% javascript %}` tags
- **Critical CSS Separation**:
  ```liquid
  {% comment %} ✅ DO: Separate critical CSS {% endcomment %}
  {{ 'critical.css' | asset_url | stylesheet_tag }}
  
  {% stylesheet %}
    /* Component-specific styles */
    .hero {
      /* Essential styles */
    }
  {% endstylesheet %}
  ```

- **CSS Variable Usage**:
  ```liquid
  {% comment %} ✅ DO: Use CSS variables for single properties {% endcomment %}
  <div style="--primary-color: {{ settings.primary_color }}; --font-size: {{ settings.font_size }}px">
  
  {% stylesheet %}
    .component {
      color: var(--primary-color);
      font-size: var(--font-size);
    }
  {% endstylesheet %}
  ```

- **CSS Classes for Multiple Properties**:
  ```liquid
  {% comment %} ✅ DO: Use classes for complex styling {% endcomment %}
  <div class="layout {{ section.settings.layout_type }}">
  
  {% stylesheet %}
    .layout--grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
      gap: 2rem;
    }
    
    .layout--flex {
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: space-between;
    }
  {% endstylesheet %}
  ```

## **Modern UX/UI Standards**
- **Responsive Design**:
  ```css
  /* ✅ DO: Mobile-first approach */
  .component {
    /* Mobile styles */
  }
  
  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .component {
      /* Tablet styles */
    }
  }
  
  @media (min-width: 1024px) {
    .component {
      /* Desktop styles */
    }
  }
  ```

- **Performance Optimizations**:
  ```liquid
  {% comment %} ✅ DO: Optimize images with responsive loading {% endcomment %}
  {% assign image_sizes = '(max-width: 767px) 100vw, (max-width: 1023px) 50vw, 33vw' %}
  {{ product.featured_image | image_url: width: 800 | image_tag: 
     loading: 'lazy', 
     sizes: image_sizes,
     widths: '300,600,800,1200' }}
  ```

- **Accessibility Standards**:
  ```liquid
  {% comment %} ✅ DO: Include proper ARIA labels and semantic HTML {% endcomment %}
  <button type="button" 
          aria-expanded="false" 
          aria-controls="mobile-menu"
          aria-label="Toggle navigation menu">
    <span class="sr-only">Menu</span>
  </button>
  ```

## **Task Management Integration**
- **Use TaskMaster MCP**: Break down theme development into manageable tasks
- **Task Structure Example**:
  ```
  1. Theme Setup & Configuration
     1.1. Initialize skeleton theme
     1.2. Configure development environment
     1.3. Set up MCP server connections
  
  2. Design System Implementation
     2.1. Create color palette variables
     2.2. Define typography system
     2.3. Build component library
  
  3. Section Development
     3.1. Header & navigation
     3.2. Hero sections
     3.3. Product showcase
     3.4. Footer
  ```

## **Store Integration**
- **Shopify MCP Server Usage**:
  - Connect to store via environment variables
  - Use for product data fetching
  - Theme installation and management
  - Real-time preview and testing

## **Quality Assurance**
- **Code Validation**:
  ```bash
  # Theme check validation
  shopify theme check
  
  # Performance testing
  shopify theme dev --store {store} --host 0.0.0.0
  ```

- **Testing Checklist**:
  - Cross-browser compatibility (Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Edge)
  - Mobile responsiveness (iOS, Android)
  - Page speed optimization
  - Accessibility compliance (WCAG 2.1)
  - SEO optimization

## **Deployment Standards**
- **Staging Process**:
  ```bash
  # Push to development theme
  shopify theme push --development
  
  # Publish to live store
  shopify theme publish
  ```

- **Version Control**: Use Git with proper branching strategy
- **Documentation**: Include README with setup instructions and feature documentation

## **Common Anti-Patterns**
```liquid
{% comment %} ❌ DON'T: Hardcode values {% endcomment %}
<div style="color: #ff0000; font-size: 16px;">

{% comment %} ❌ DON'T: Skip schema definitions {% endcomment %}
<!-- Section without {% schema %} -->

{% comment %} ❌ DON'T: Inline large CSS blocks {% endcomment %}
<style>
  /* Hundreds of lines of CSS */
</style>

{% comment %} ❌ DON'T: Ignore accessibility {% endcomment %}
<div onclick="toggleMenu()">Menu</div>
```

